## Development

```bash
pnpm test       # run tests
pnpm build      # compile TypeScript
pnpm start      # run compiled output
```

## Security note

This server uses the MCP stdio transport. In production deployments, the MCP client (Claude Desktop, Claude Code, Cursor, etc.) spawns this process directly — stdio is local and trusted by design. If you expose this server over a network boundary in the future, add authentication (OAuth 2.1 + PKCE per the MCP spec) at that layer.

